<L>__{exterior gray's inn office day}
<A>__{the coach drives up.}
<C>__{roderick }
<D>__{we were in london at three o'clock, an half an hour before the time appointed.}
<L>__{interior staircase day}
<A>__{roderick and the countess looking for the office.}
<C>__{roderick }
<D>__{i easily found out mr. tapewell's apartment: a gloomy den it was, and in an unlucky hour, i entered it.}
<A>__{they climb up dirty backstairs, lit by a feeble lamp, and the dim sky of a dismal london afternoon. the countess seems agitated and fainterior when they get to the door, she stops in front of it.}
<C>__{countess}
<D>__{roderick don't go in. i am sure there is danger. there's time yet, let us go back anywhere!}
<A>__{the countess has put herself before the door in a theatrical attitude and takes roderick's hand. he pushes her away to one side.}
<C>__{roderick}
<D>__{lady cosgrove, you are an old fool.}
<C>__{countess}
<D>__{old fool!}
<A>__{she jumps at the bell, which is quickly answered by a moldy looking gentleman in an unpowered wig.}
<C>__{countess}
<D>__{say lady cosgrove is here!}
<A>__{she stalks down the passage, muttering: "old fool."}
